The article describes the author's childhood memories of ice skating on the frozen canals of the Delaware River during winter. They mention how the ordinary town and bridge would transform into a sparkling landscape filled with magic. This inspired the White House holiday theme, which includes an ice rink on the South Lawn. The author expresses the hope that visitors to the White House will enjoy their time and create lasting memories. The article also acknowledges the organizations that made the ice rink possible, such as the National Park Service, National Park Foundation, Comcast, NHL, NHL Players Association, and Riedell. The author concludes by asking who is ready to skate.